551
00:39:36,164 --> 00:39:39,944
The memorial service...
- What memorial service?

552
00:39:41,835 --> 00:39:45,247
Friends, we are gathered here today

553
00:39:45,380 --> 00:39:49,374
in remembrance
of our missing friend, Poppy.

554
00:39:49,508 --> 00:39:51,298
Oh, Poppy...

555
00:39:52,303 --> 00:39:55,882
Wherever you have chosen
to sow your seeds,

556
00:39:56,015 --> 00:39:58,681
we pray that you are blooming.

557
00:39:58,808 --> 00:40:01,475
We pray that you have gone
to a better place.

558
00:40:01,603 --> 00:40:05,099
Shame we don't know
exactly where that place is...

559
00:40:05,231 --> 00:40:08,762
Anyway, now for a eulogy
from Emily Dickinson, queen of mirth.

560
00:40:10,986 --> 00:40:15,809
"Because I could not stop for death,
he kindly stopped for me.

561
00:40:15,949 --> 00:40:19,859
"The carriage held but just ourselves
and immortality."

562
00:40:19,994 --> 00:40:24,782
Or maybe the carriage didn't stop
and Poppy got squished.

563
00:40:24,915 --> 00:40:27,368
Scraped off the road
and put in a sausage...

564
00:40:27,502 --> 00:40:30,334
Oh, Hilda!

565
00:40:38,553 --> 00:40:40,840
Thank you, Mr Gribble.

566
00:40:41,596 --> 00:40:45,175
Now, ladies and gentlemen,
boys and girls,

567
00:40:45,309 --> 00:40:49,800
behold Reverend Burton
and Marion Whittaker

568
00:40:49,938 --> 00:40:55,093
