605
00:44:44,023 --> 00:44:47,768
I'm completely humiliated!
I'll never get a husband now!

606
00:44:47,901 --> 00:44:50,306
After tonight, I'd have thought
they'll be lining up round the block.

607
00:44:50,445 --> 00:44:53,609
I hate her! Hate, hate, hate her!

608
00:44:55,366 --> 00:44:58,731
The advance notices
are sensational, Mrs John.

609
00:45:09,171 --> 00:45:13,958
Is it my imagination or is the cutlery
particularly deafening this evening?

610
00:45:14,091 --> 00:45:17,955
I don't know how many times
I have to say this, Hilda. I am sorry.

611
00:45:18,094 --> 00:45:22,586
That's easy for you to say.
- It's surprisingly hard to be easy.

612
00:45:24,016 --> 00:45:27,880
You're smiling, Jim.
- God forbid, the wind might change.

613
00:45:30,607 --> 00:45:34,186
Hilda, if I had any inkling that you
were going to take me seriously...

614
00:45:34,318 --> 00:45:36,558
You could have made an effort
to enjoy it less.

615
00:45:36,695 --> 00:45:40,274
I had my underpants on.
I was having a grand time.

616
00:45:41,574 --> 00:45:46,776
It's not fair! You've got two husbands,
and I've had none.

617
00:45:46,913 --> 00:45:49,827
Technically, I have one.
- But you've had two.

618
00:45:49,956 --> 00:45:52,410
I've had two shoes
and it's a great deal more practical.

619
00:45:52,543 --> 00:45:56,074
I dare say you've worn down
more soles than that.

620
00:45:59,091 --> 00:46:01,081
John...

621
00:46:01,217 --> 00:46:04,796
Marion, Larita's first husband died
of cancer. Stop being so callous.

622
00:46:04,928 --> 00:46:07,595
Oh, I'm sure Marion
can appreciate the pain

623
00:46:07,723 --> 00:46:10,507
of watching a loved one
slip through her fingers.

624
00:46:10,641 --> 00:46:12,632
She's scandalous!

625
00:46:13,979 --> 00:46:16,847
