sanction divorce.

673
00:49:16,142 --> 00:49:19,508
The Lord is Almighty, Marion.
He can sanction anything he likes.

674
00:49:19,645 --> 00:49:21,553
The sooner they move out
the better.

675
00:49:21,689 --> 00:49:25,386
They move out?
John isn't going anywhere.

676
00:49:25,525 --> 00:49:27,350
Watch and learn.

677
00:49:32,865 --> 00:49:36,147
It's so unfair.
Why can't I have a room like this?

678
00:49:39,371 --> 00:49:42,701
I could die of envy!

679
00:49:42,833 --> 00:49:45,286
Laying to rest this tragic incident,

680
00:49:45,419 --> 00:49:49,329
we've had this splendid set of rooms
made over for you, haven't we, Jim?

681
00:49:49,463 --> 00:49:52,663
Yes. My wife would like you
to rest in peace.

682
00:49:52,800 --> 00:49:56,841
I even had an old friend of Johnnie's
brought down from the attic.

683
00:49:56,970 --> 00:49:59,589
"Old Faithful Awaits
His Master's Return".

684
00:49:59,723 --> 00:50:02,638
I used to sleep under
that silly painting.

685
00:50:02,767 --> 00:50:05,599
Very comforting, I'm sure,
but we're expected back in Mayfair.

686
00:50:05,728 --> 00:50:08,596
But these are the largest rooms
in the house.

687
00:50:08,731 --> 00:50:10,805
You'll find nothing like it in London.

688
00:50:10,940 --> 00:50:13,014
She has a point.
- She always does.

689
00:50:13,151 --> 00:50:16,314
Sometimes I don't know
why you ever did wander home.

690
00:50:16,446 --> 00:50:17,986
And miss all the fun?

691
00:50:18,614 --> 00:50:21,281
Cook would like to inform you,
Mrs Whittaker, the bird is stuffed.

692
00:50:21,409 --> 00:50:23,199
Oh!

693
00:50:23,328 --> 00:50:25,402
What bird, hmm?

694
00:50:25,538 --> 00:50:28,453
Thursday is bubble and squeak.
I hadn't made any arrangements.

695
00:50:28,583 --> 00:50:30,620
Oh, but I have!

696
00:50:36,088 --> 00:50:40,212
In appreciation of your understanding
and for that delicious double bed.

697
00:50:40,342 --> 00:50:43,210
We'll think of you every time we use it.

698
00:50:50,435 --> 00:50:53,635
What exactly are we celebrating?
- Thanksgiving.

699
00:50:53,772 --> 00:50:55,809
Thanks for what, hmm?

700
00:50:55,940 --> 00:50:59,519
The annihilation
of an entire indigenous people.

701
00:50:59,651 --> 00:51:02,566
A loving union of two great cultures.

702
00:51:02,696 --> 00:51:05,694
Just like us.
- How transcontinental.

703
00:51:05,824 --> 00:51:08,905
I can't believe you got into the kitchen.
- Beatrice did put up a fight.

704
00:51:09,034 --> 00:51:12,281
But technically I outrank her.
- Who's Beatrice?

705
00:51:12,413 --> 00:51:17,829
Your cook. Or now my undercook,
since I'm qualified cordon bleu.

706
00:51:17,960 --> 00:51:20,116
That's a degree.

707
00:51:20,253 --> 00:51:24,827
Furber... take the vegetables down to
the kitchen and tell Cook to cook them.

708
00:51:24,966 --> 00:51:29,458
No, Furber, thank you.
I think I'll surprise my alimentary canal.

709
00:51:30,638 --> 00:51:34,134
Mother, if you don't mind, I'm going
to eat my meal before it gets cold.

710
00:51:34,266 --> 00:51:36,304
Furber, I've changed my mind,
bring it back!

711
00:51:36,435 --> 00:51:37,548
Me, too.

712
00:51:39,520 --> 00:51:41,594
Gobble, gobble!

713
00:51:46,861 --> 00:51:48,318
Yes!

714
00:51:52,282 --> 00:51:53,905
Here's a tip, Hilda.

715
00:51:54,033 --> 00:51:57,481
A sure way to a man's heart is
through his stomach. Or his mother.

716
00:51:57,621 --> 00:52:01,994
Larita, look, I've found
another likeness of Edgar.

717
00:52:02,125 --> 00:52:05,786
Marion, this is Fatty Arbuckle.
- Who's in jail, I know that.

718
00:52:05,919 --> 00:52:09,249
But if you cut out his cheeks
and give him a bald patch,

719
00:52:09,380 --> 00:52:11,869
there's a striking resemblance...

720
00:52:12,008 --> 00:52:14,923
Edgar's away on a trip
across the pond,

721
00:52:15,053 --> 00:52:18,004
sewing his wild oats,
or something agricultural.

722
00:52:19,599 --> 00:52:23,544
She's good, I'll give her that.
- I think you're over-reacting.

723
00:52:30,274 --> 00:52:32,845
Lari? Lari!

724
00:52:33,861 --> 00:52:36,528
Not the vase! Not the vase!

725
00:52:36,655 --> 00:52:40,067
"Taking the corncockle buds
and bee-kissed roses

726
00:52:40,200 --> 00:52:42,274
"roughly in his calloused hands,

727
00:52:42,411 --> 00:52:47,910
"his hot, moist tulip exploded
in her river of delights..."

728
00:52:59,050 --> 00:53:01,005
Larita?

729
00:53:01,135 --> 00:53:03,256
Early Christmas present...

730
00:53:03,387 --> 00:53:06,634
For you, darling.
- Ooh, the mind boggles.

731
00:53:14,481 --> 00:53:15,938
Well, it's... it's...

732
00:53:16,065 --> 00:53:18,056
It's magnificent.
It's monstrous!

733
00:53:18,192 --> 00:53:22,731
It's me. I posed for a young Spaniard.
Don't you absolutely adore it?

734
00:53:22,863 --> 00:53:25,980
Very expressive, darling,
but I can't quite see you in it.

735
00:53:26,116 --> 00:53:27,657
You can see
everything else!

736
00:53:27,784 --> 00:53:30,533
You took your clothes off
in front of a total stranger?

737
00:53:30,662 --> 00:53:34,526
Of course she took her clothes off.
- I think it's unholy.

738
00:53:34,666 --> 00:53:40,165
I'm not sure I approve of you being nude.
You know, without... without me.

739
00:53:40,295 --> 00:53:41,752
Extraordinary.

740
00:53:42,923 --> 00:53:45,791
What exactly are you
hoping to achieve?

741
00:53:45,926 --> 00:53:48,711
Just trying to get into the swing
of things... Mother.

742
00:53:48,845 --> 00:53:54,675
Marvellous! Well, then, you'll be riding
in the hunt with us, won't you?

743
00:53:54,808 --> 00:53:57,842
I might be persuaded
if the painting stays.

744
00:53:57,978 --> 00:53:59,720
Hunt.
- Paint.

745
00:53:59,855 --> 00:54:01,597
Hunt.
- Paint.

746
00:54:01,731 --> 00:54:03,224
Hunt!

747
00:54:03,358 --> 00:54:05,017
Very well.

748
00:54:06,986 --> 00:54:08,479
Hunt.

749
00:54:14,284 --> 00:54:16,109
View, hello.

750
00:54:19,372 --> 00:54:23,069
Hello, everyone.
Good to see you. Richard.

751
00:54:23,209 --> 00:54:26,622
Morning, Jim!
After generations of false starts,

752
00:54:26,754 --> 00:54:29,373
we've finally managed
to combine our cavalry.

753
00:54:29,507 --> 00:54:32,209
Congratulations.
A marriage of minor convenience.

754
00:54:32,342 --> 00:54:34,167
You'll be fine, I promise.

755
00:54:34,303 --> 00:54:38,960
The second you have the Holborough
boy's eye, flirt outrageously.

756
00:54:39,098 --> 00:54:41,800
But Warwick Holborough has ears
like the Cambridge Cup!

757
00:54:41,935 --> 00:54:47,137
And Philip's the prize. Now, if you want
a man's attention... ignore him.

758
00:54:54,362 --> 00:54:57,609
Warwick the Wingnut
and Sausage Fingers?

759
00:54:57,741 --> 00:55:01,983
What a handsome couple.
They'll have puppies not children.

760
00:55:03,954 --> 00:55:07,818
Wait... there's something I need to say.

761
00:55:08,959 --> 00:55:12,325
I see you... you're wasted here.

762
00:55:12,462 --> 00:55:16,290
When the time comes... give me a ring.

763
00:55:16,424 --> 00:55:19,375
If I could find your neck, I'd wring it.

764
00:55:19,509 --> 00:55:23,420
Larita's making sheep's eyes at Philip.
- She's a Venus de Flytrap!

765
00:55:23,555 --> 00:55:27,679
She wants him all to herself.
- She's not interested in Philip.

766
00:55:27,809 --> 00:55:30,179
Nobody's interested in Philip.
- I am!

767
00:55:31,145 --> 00:55:32,887
Mount up, Larita.

768
00:55:33,021 --> 00:55:36,932
If you don't mind, I think
I might give the fox a head start.

769
00:55:37,067 --> 00:55:39,982
Lari, get on the pony, please.

770
00:55:40,570 --> 00:55:42,726
Oh, it's just as I thought...

771
00:55:42,864 --> 00:55:46,312
Oh, I said I'd ride,
and I'm always good for my word.

772
00:55:47,326 --> 00:55:48,570
Tally-ho!

773
00:56:04,508 --> 00:56:08,454
# Spy on me, baby, use satellite

774
00:56:08,596 --> 00:56:12,636
# Infrared to see me
move through the night

775
00:56:12,765 --> 00:56:16,261
# Aim, going to fire, shoot me right

776
00:56:16,393 --> 00:56:20,304
# I'm going to like the way you fight

777
00:56:20,439 --> 00:56:24,515
# Now you've found
the secret code I use

778
00:56:24,651 --> 00:56:28,479
# To wash away my lonely blues

779
00:56:28,613 --> 00:56:34,977
# So I can't deny or lie
cos you're the only one to make me fly

780
00:56:36,162 --> 00:56:40,452
# Sex bomb, sex bomb,
you're a sex bomb

781
00:56:40,582 --> 00:56:43,864
# You can give it to me
when I need to come along...

782
00:56:44,002 --> 00:56:46,408
What?

783
00:56:46,546 --> 00:56:48,833
# You're my sex bomb... #

784
00:56:48,965 --> 00:56:52,295
What is she doing?
- A victory lap, by the look of things.

785
00:56:53,344 --> 00:56:56,875
There's something wild about that child
that's so contagious.

786
00:57:00,308 --> 00:57:02,465
Whoo-hoo!

787
00:57:05,688 --> 00:57:09,729
Well, she promised she'd ride.
Ha-ha!

788
00:57:18,991 --> 00:57:22,606
#... no chaperone
can get our number

789
00:57:22,744 --> 00:57:27,781
# The world's in a slumber,
let's misbehave!

790
00:57:27,917 --> 00:57:32,705
# There's something wild
about you, child, that's so contagious

791
00:57:32,838 --> 00:57:37,958
# Let's be outrageous,
let's misbehave!

792
00:57:38,092 --> 00:57:42,833
# When Adam won Eve's hand,
he wouldn't stand for teasin'

793
00:57:42,971 --> 00:57:47,794
# He didn't care about those apples
out of season

794
00:57:47,934 --> 00:57:52,840
# They say that Spring means
just one little thing to little lovebirds

795
00:57:52,980 --> 00:57:58,562
# We're not above birds,
let's misbehave... #

796
00:58:04,867 --> 00:58:06,443
Whoo!

797
00:58:16,918 --> 00:58:19,585
Miss Hilda,
telephone from New York.

798
00:58:27,178 --> 00:58:28,670
Uncle George?

799
00:58:28,805 --> 00:58:31,672
Oh, thank God, a friendly voice.

800
00:58:31,808 --> 00:58:34,924
Yes, and she's a complete nightmare.

801
00:58:37,687 --> 00:58:39,678
Really?

802
00:58:39,814 --> 00:58:42,018
How salacious.

803
00:58:44,401 --> 00:58:46,273
Come in.

804
00:58:47,196 --> 00:58:48,653
Mother?

805
00:58:50,032 --> 00:58:53,279
I'd like to apologise
for today's schmozzle.

806
00:58:53,409 --> 00:58:55,696
That really won't be necessary.

807
00:58:55,828 --> 00:58:58,992
Larita made no secret
of her disapproval of blood sports.

808
00:58:59,123 --> 00:59:00,699
She did ride as promised.

809
00:59:00,833 --> 00:59:06,284
Well, we should credit her with her
imaginative way of keeping her word.

810
00:59:06,422 --> 00:59:08,496
You must be very proud of her.

811
00:59:09,549 --> 00:59:12,120
Mother, I think...

812
00:59:12,259 --> 00:59:14,748
I think maybe Larita and I ought to go.

813
00:59:14,887 --> 00:59:17,091
Oh...

814
00:59:17,224 --> 00:59:19,842
Yes, I see. Very well.

815
00:59:19,976 --> 00:59:23,804
Feel free to drop in
whenever it takes your fancy.

816
00:59:23,937 --> 00:59:26,141
Off you go. Enjoy.
- Don't be like that.

817
00:59:26,272 --> 00:59:29,270
I'm sorry, dear,
wasn't Mummy being kind enough?

818
00:59:29,401 --> 00:59:31,889
Take these, they might get you
as far as Constantinople!

819
00:59:32,028 --> 00:59:34,694
And this... Casablanca.
- Mother, stop it!

820
00:59:34,822 --> 00:59:36,694
No. You stop it!

821
00:59:38,075 --> 00:59:40,149
Stop being so naïve!

822
00:59:47,041 --> 00:59:49,529
The money's gone, John.

823
00:59:49,668 --> 00:59:51,623
Nothing left.

824
00:59:51,753 --> 00:59:54,953
The only thing standing
between this family and bankruptcy

825
00:59:55,091 --> 00:59:57,579
are those surveyors in the back field.

826
00:59:59,344 --> 01:00:04,962
Lord Hurst is offering to buy 400 acres
to keep the bailiffs away.

827
01:00:06,559 --> 01:00:11,016
It's your legacy, John Whittaker...
and I'm selling it.

828
01:00:15,609 --> 01:00:20,266
I had no idea.
- No... No, you don't.

829
01:00:25,159 --> 01:00:29,366
You were supposed to take over
the estate, take your responsibilities.

830
01:00:29,496 --> 01:00:32,494
But you were unexpectedly
flagged down.

831
01:00:34,209 --> 01:00:37,290
I've been struggling for years
with a man who doesn't care,

832
01:00:37,420 --> 01:00:39,624
waiting for you to step up to the mark.

833
01:00:42,133 --> 01:00:45,249
No. You just go.

834
01:00:45,385 --> 01:00:48,750
Go to Algiers
with your racing car driver.

835
01:00:48,889 --> 01:00:51,555
I'm too tired to care any more!

836
01:00:53,726 --> 01:00:57,423
It's not exactly surprising,
John. Look at the grounds.

837
01:00:57,563 --> 01:01:02,019
Your mother is being very practical.
- In what sense?

838
01:01:02,150 --> 01:01:05,516
You're not coming back.
Your father moved out decades ago.

839
01:01:05,653 --> 01:01:09,647
Philip's not going to marry Hilda.
Nobody's going to marry Marion.

840
01:01:09,782 --> 01:01:13,823
Subdividing the land and selling
to a neighbour is an elegant solution.

841
01:01:13,953 --> 01:01:15,611
Somewhat harsh.

842
01:01:17,123 --> 01:01:19,825
I've had my fair share
of selling off my past,

843
01:01:19,958 --> 01:01:24,082
and it is an auction of innocence
that's neither fun nor pretty,

844
01:01:24,212 --> 01:01:27,625
but it is realistic,
something your mother excels in.

845
01:01:27,756 --> 01:01:30,458
But it's my responsibility.

846
01:01:31,886 --> 01:01:35,049
Gracious, how can I have been so blind?

847
01:02:13,464 --> 01:02:16,877
Oh, winter hydrangeas!
How do you do it?

848
01:02:17,009 --> 01:02:21,797
It's a controlled mixture of passion,
persistence and horse manure.

849
01:02:24,516 --> 01:02:27,929
I was hoping to catch a glimpse
of the new bride.

850
01:02:28,061 --> 01:02:31,557
Ah! John's wife has
very fickle allergies.

851
01:02:31,689 --> 01:02:36,311
Allergies to what?
- Flowers, Emma. Can you believe it?

852
01:02:36,443 --> 01:02:39,607
That is a strange choice of bed fellow
for this neck of the woods.

853
01:02:39,738 --> 01:02:43,068
You'll just have to make do
with John and Sarah.

854
01:02:43,199 --> 01:02:45,688
It'll be like old times.

855
01:02:45,826 --> 01:02:51,361
# When you're smiling,
the whole world smiles... #

856
01:02:53,041 --> 01:02:55,364
Why the big Panda eyes?

857
01:02:57,213 --> 01:02:59,997
I've often meant to ask you something,
but I hadn't the courage.

858
01:03:00,131 --> 01:03:02,205
Well, don't then.

859
01:03:02,342 --> 01:03:06,631
Did you think I behaved like a cad,
marrying Larita without telling you?

860
01:03:06,761 --> 01:03:08,752
No, of course not.

861
01:03:08,889 --> 01:03:12,551
You took the opportunity and married
for love. I respect you for it.

862
01:03:12,684 --> 01:03:16,050
If we'd have married it would've been
for friendship and convenience.

863
01:03:16,187 --> 01:03:18,308
Would it?
- Yes!

864
01:03:18,439 --> 01:03:20,928
We knew one another far too well.

865
01:03:21,066 --> 01:03:27,015
I want my marriage to be thrilling,
romantic, with passionate love letters.

866
01:03:27,156 --> 01:03:30,817
I could've written you love letters.
- Well, you didn't, did you?

867
01:03:30,951 --> 01:03:33,025
I did love you all the same.

868
01:03:34,412 --> 01:03:35,821
John, stop it.

869
01:03:44,963 --> 01:03:47,961
He's very different
from the man I met in France.

870
01:03:49,342 --> 01:03:53,834
The boy. The same, sweet boy.

871
01:03:57,808 --> 01:04:02,347
Is it true what she says?
Are you really selling off the land?

872
01:04:03,938 --> 01:04:07,683
To be perfectly honest,
I haven't the faintest idea.

873
01:04:10,152 --> 01:04:12,936
But it's your home, it's your community.

874
01:04:14,156 --> 01:04:16,028
Doesn't that matter?

875
01:04:16,157 --> 01:04:17,733
No.

876
01:04:19,536 --> 01:04:21,657
You're a dark horse.

877
01:04:24,249 --> 01:04:29,155
Have you noticed how few men
of my age there are in this village?

878
01:04:29,295 --> 01:04:32,412
Fourteen years ago,
we all took the King's shilling.

879
01:04:32,547 --> 01:04:35,332
We all signed up together.

880
01:04:35,467 --> 01:04:40,420
My brother, friends, staff...

881
01:04:41,889 --> 01:04:46,630
All hunkered down in the front row
of The Great War.

882
01:04:47,978 --> 01:04:51,558
I thought they kept majors
safely behind desks?

883
01:04:51,690 --> 01:04:53,976
Promotion for surviving.

884
01:04:55,818 --> 01:05:00,143
As captain, it was my job
to get them all out of the trenches.

885
01:05:00,280 --> 01:05:04,440
Within the first four minutes
of our first charge...

886
01:05:06,578 --> 01:05:08,734
...20,000 men died.

887
01:05:14,127 --> 01:05:16,532
In Thorverton, down the road here...

888
01:05:17,672 --> 01:05:20,125
...they were stationed in Morocco.

889
01:05:21,049 --> 01:05:23,537
Their captain bought them all home.

890
01:05:29,473 --> 01:05:32,471
I didn't bring a single man back.

891
01:05:33,310 --> 01:05:35,431
This whole village died.

892
01:05:36,396 --> 01:05:39,809
I think there's a glimmer
of life in you yet.

893
01:05:39,941 --> 01:05:44,764
Well, if there is, it has no time for
pet cemeteries and Japanese lanterns.

894
01:05:44,904 --> 01:05:48,352
Why did you come back?
- I had no choice.

895
01:05:51,869 --> 01:05:56,028
Bonjour, Madame.
Qu'est-ce que vous voulez?

896
01:06:04,922 --> 01:06:07,245
'She came for you? '

897
01:06:08,843 --> 01:06:10,252
Why the lie?

898
01:06:10,384 --> 01:06:13,916
She thought "wandering home"
sounded better.

899
01:06:16,558 --> 01:06:19,225
And to be perfectly frank,
I no longer cared.

900
01:06:24,774 --> 01:06:29,478
I hate new games. There are
too many balls, I can't sink anything.

901
01:06:29,610 --> 01:06:33,686
Sink some gin, Sausage Fingers!
- I never, ever win.

902
01:06:33,823 --> 01:06:35,814
Oh, well done!

903
01:06:41,956 --> 01:06:45,570
Stop sucking it. Come and help.
Come on, Pops.

904
01:06:45,709 --> 01:06:49,039
All right, Missie,
hold your horses.

905
01:06:49,170 --> 01:06:51,575
Right, clear the decks, puppies.

906
01:06:51,714 --> 01:06:53,539
May I?

907
01:07:00,889 --> 01:07:03,377
I was hoping to have a word.

908
01:07:03,516 --> 01:07:07,675
We're accentuating the positive today,
I don't have a mind for anything else.

909
01:07:07,811 --> 01:07:09,767
Of course... of course.

910
01:07:11,273 --> 01:07:13,939
I know you are
under considerable stress...

911
01:07:15,736 --> 01:07:17,608
Regarding what?

912
01:07:19,280 --> 01:07:22,692
Lord Hurst's kind offer
to buy into your property.

913
01:07:22,825 --> 01:07:26,818
The realtor I'm dealing with in London
also specialises in subdivision.

914
01:07:26,955 --> 01:07:31,446
Perhaps he could help negotiate
a premium price.

915
01:07:31,583 --> 01:07:35,114
Thank you, but really this is
of no concern of yours.

916
01:07:35,253 --> 01:07:39,495
Of course it's a concern. I am a member
of this family now and I'd like to help.

917
01:07:39,633 --> 01:07:42,796
And this is your interpretation
of "help", is it?

918
01:07:42,927 --> 01:07:46,293
Carving up our heritage and selling
it off to the highest bidder?

919
01:07:46,429 --> 01:07:49,000
Coming from a country no older
than the chair you are sitting in,

920
01:07:49,141 --> 01:07:51,178
it seems a very practical solution.

921
01:07:51,310 --> 01:07:53,928
Just forget the seven
generations of people

922
01:07:54,062 --> 01:07:57,806
who have devoted their entire lives
to farming this land.

923
01:07:57,940 --> 01:08:01,103
Get someone else to do it.
With a machine, no less.

924
01:08:02,152 --> 01:08:04,226
Who do you think you are?

925
01:08:05,447 --> 01:08:09,227
Swinging your wherewithal
like a cat on heat.

926
01:08:10,701 --> 01:08:14,197
If you really want to be
of assistance, Larita,

927
01:08:14,330 --> 01:08:16,901
I think you know what's required.

928
01:08:19,042 --> 01:08:21,080
Right...

929
01:08:21,211 --> 01:08:25,039
I think it's time an expert showed you
how this game is played.

930
01:08:25,173 --> 01:08:27,163
Watch it...

931
01:08:27,300 --> 01:08:28,757
Bravo!

932
01:08:30,178 --> 01:08:34,124
What a sportswoman, I must say.
Can you imagine? Fantastic!

933
01:08:36,308 --> 01:08:38,382
'Lari, you're confusing me.'

934
01:08:38,518 --> 01:08:41,516
'I'm feeling trapped.'
- 'I don't understand.'

935
01:08:41,646 --> 01:08:44,810
It's this house!
It has an air of doom hanging over it.

936
01:08:44,941 --> 01:08:48,058
And I can barely stand the weight
much longer.

937
01:08:53,741 --> 01:08:56,608
The answer is to go abroad again.

938
01:08:56,743 --> 01:09:01,317
Not yet. This is my life for now,
you know that.

939
01:09:01,455 --> 01:09:04,702
And what part do I play in it?
- Do you have to be so loud?

940
01:09:04,833 --> 01:09:07,618
Of course I do! I'm American.

941
01:09:13,383 --> 01:09:18,005
What is the use of bickering like this?
It doesn't lead anywhere.

942
01:09:18,137 --> 01:09:21,088
You never know.
It might lead to a natural end.

943
01:09:22,724 --> 01:09:24,844
Do you want it to?

944
01:09:25,977 --> 01:09:28,216
Do you?

945
01:09:28,355 --> 01:09:29,812
No!

946
01:09:30,648 --> 01:09:33,765
I just want some peace and quiet.

947
01:09:33,901 --> 01:09:36,686
You're far too young
to make a remark like that.

948
01:09:36,820 --> 01:09:38,894
I can't help my age...

949
01:09:40,198 --> 01:09:42,106
...Grandma.

950
01:09:44,994 --> 01:09:50,529
Look, I'm sorry that I leave you alone
so much. Honestly, I'm sorry.

951
01:09:53,043 --> 01:09:56,539
Good. Then let's do something about it.

952
01:10:01,926 --> 01:10:04,379
Why are we driving so fast?

953
01:10:04,511 --> 01:10:06,585
The thrill of escape!

954
01:10:11,519 --> 01:10:14,931
You're looking very game today.
Fairest game in the land.

955
01:10:16,481 --> 01:10:18,139
A penny for your thoughts?

956
01:10:18,275 --> 01:10:20,977
It's more than pennies,
I'm afraid, Pinkie.

957
01:10:21,110 --> 01:10:23,563
I don't think I can afford the party
this year.

958
01:10:23,695 --> 01:10:26,314
But the Japanese lanterns!
- No, cancelled.

959
01:10:26,449 --> 01:10:29,316
Had to choose,
Japanese lanterns or the maid.

960
01:10:29,451 --> 01:10:34,688
You're not getting out of it that easily.
My offer of cellar and staff still stands.

961
01:10:34,831 --> 01:10:38,362
It wouldn't be Christmas
without your knees-up.

962
01:10:48,885 --> 01:10:54,384
Oh! This is the first piece of clarity
I've had since arriving. Whoo!

963
01:10:58,019 --> 01:11:01,680
Why can't we live in moments
like these forever?

964
01:11:01,813 --> 01:11:03,684
Why?

965
01:11:03,815 --> 01:11:07,180
Because you've stopped
loving me, my darling!

966
01:11:07,318 --> 01:11:09,355
How can you say that?

967
01:11:09,487 --> 01:11:12,485
Oh, I just open my mouth
and the words come out.

968
01:11:13,407 --> 01:11:15,611
Then let's make a fresh start.

969
01:11:31,006 --> 01:11:35,912
There are so many things I need
to tell you about me. Hard things.

970
01:11:36,053 --> 01:11:37,842
I don't care.

971
01:11:37,970 --> 01:11:39,842
I do.

972
01:11:39,972 --> 01:11:44,345
It doesn't matter.
I trust you absolutely.

973
01:11:44,811 --> 01:11:54,434
# I'll see you again
whenever Spring breaks through again...

974
01:11:54,569 --> 01:11:55,848
Come on.

975
01:11:56,696 --> 01:12:00,986
# Time may lie heavy between

976
01:12:01,826 --> 01:12:08,736
# But what has been
is past forgetting

977
01:12:08,874 --> 01:12:13,863
# This sweet memory

978
01:12:14,003 --> 01:12:20,450
# Throughout my life will come to me

979
01:12:20,592 --> 01:12:25,084
# Though the world may go awry... #

980
01:12:27,599 --> 01:12:28,842
Shot!

981
01:12:36,940 --> 01:12:38,397
John!

982
01:12:42,069 --> 01:12:45,399
Top hole.
- Oh!

983
01:12:45,532 --> 01:12:48,778
I can't decide which is worse,
that you had to sneak outside

984
01:12:48,910 --> 01:12:51,694
to get some privacy,
or that you were caught by Veronica.

985
01:12:51,828 --> 01:12:53,653
Who's Veronica?

986
01:12:53,789 --> 01:12:56,028
I am. It's my name.

987
01:12:59,210 --> 01:13:02,706
I fail to see the humour in it!
- No, darling, you're quite right.

988
01:13:02,839 --> 01:13:06,204
I can certainly see the serious
implications. It's not a laughing matter.

989
01:13:06,342 --> 01:13:08,213
It's only a laughing matter.

990
01:13:08,344 --> 01:13:12,207
Indecent exposure is illegal.
Even in America.

991
01:13:12,347 --> 01:13:14,421
Yep, yep...

992
01:13:14,557 --> 01:13:17,128
You're right.
And we're very, very sorry, aren't we?

993
01:13:17,267 --> 01:13:21,557
No, I'm not. This is my husband.
- And this is my home!

994
01:13:21,689 --> 01:13:24,178
Maybe it's time for them
to fly the nest?

995
01:13:24,316 --> 01:13:28,180
Certainly not. They will stay put
and brazen this out.

996
01:13:28,319 --> 01:13:31,317
And you can get that ghastly painting
out of my house!

997
01:13:31,448 --> 01:13:34,316
We do not need any more reminders
of your easy virtue!

998
01:13:44,626 --> 01:13:47,162
Excited, Furber?
- Overwhelmed, sir.

999
01:13:47,295 --> 01:13:51,869
Miss Hilda...
- Uncle George... How explosive!

1000
01:13:52,007 --> 01:13:54,710
Furber, I recognise that as asparagus.

1001
01:13:54,844 --> 01:13:56,716
Correct, Madam.

1002
01:13:56,846 --> 01:14:00,425
Ha! I pity poor Panda.
- Oh, what is it now?

1003
01:14:00,557 --> 01:14:05,713
Read! "The Detroit News".
Uncle George is a super sleuth!

1004
01:14:05,854 --> 01:14:09,267
Collecting old newspapers is
the last refuge of a truly boring man.

1005
01:14:09,398 --> 01:14:13,522
Boring? Far from it. It was a scandal!

1006
01:14:13,652 --> 01:14:16,354
Wasn't it... Mrs Morley?

1007
01:14:17,655 --> 01:14:20,772
Mrs Tom Morley of Detroit, Michigan.

1008
01:14:20,908 --> 01:14:23,112
Don't be grotesque, Hilda.

1009
01:14:23,244 --> 01:14:27,736
Well, I suppose I'd better finish
my meal before it wilts entirely.

1010
01:14:27,872 --> 01:14:30,326
Any dressing?
- Oh, I am genuinely shocked!

1011
01:14:30,459 --> 01:14:34,156
No thanks, I always end up wearing it.
- We've been hoodwinked!

1012
01:14:34,296 --> 01:14:36,702
Especially that runny vinaigrette.
- Fire and brimstone!

1013
01:14:36,839 --> 01:14:38,794
Mayonnaise has more ballast.

1014
01:14:38,924 --> 01:14:42,290
Will you stop this insulting behaviour
immediately?

1015
01:14:48,058 --> 01:14:50,178
Oh, I always hated that photo of myself.

1016
01:14:50,310 --> 01:14:54,386
Of everything I ever
expected, nothing prepared me for this.

1017
01:14:54,523 --> 01:14:57,190
For what?
- She was charged with murder.

1018
01:14:57,316 --> 01:14:59,804
I was acquitted.
- And that's consolation?

1019
01:14:59,944 --> 01:15:03,392
I told you my husband died.
- But you didn't tell us how, did you?

1020
01:15:03,530 --> 01:15:05,521
Does John know about this?

1021
01:15:05,657 --> 01:15:07,980
I see...
- It's no concern of ours.

1022
01:15:08,118 --> 01:15:10,736
Father! Really!

1023
01:15:10,870 --> 01:15:13,737
Yes, and after Hilda went
to all that trouble digging it up.

1024
01:15:13,873 --> 01:15:16,326
I'm going outside for a cigarette.
Care to join me?

1025
01:15:16,459 --> 01:15:19,374
Thank you, Jim. Don't mind if I do.

1026
01:15:21,130 --> 01:15:22,836
No concern?

1027
01:15:28,178 --> 01:15:30,252
The pack's closing.

1028
01:15:30,388 --> 01:15:33,552
This woman has taken advantage
of our son!

1029
01:15:33,683 --> 01:15:35,720
He'd never have married her
if he'd known.

1030
01:15:35,850 --> 01:15:38,718
You know that, do you?
- You'd have preferred we had an affair?

1031
01:15:38,854 --> 01:15:41,935
It would've been more appropriate!
- Mother!

1032
01:15:42,065 --> 01:15:46,141
Unfortunately, I agree with you!
- It's easy to talk like this now.

1033
01:15:46,276 --> 01:15:50,352
It isn't easy, it's heartbreaking.
I love John, but it's not blind love.

1034
01:15:51,866 --> 01:15:54,817
Marion, does that sound
indicate contempt or asthma?

1035
01:15:54,951 --> 01:15:57,274
You can't palm us off like that,
Mrs Morley.

1036
01:15:57,412 --> 01:15:59,486
This is your doing.
You're a bigger fool than you look.

1037
01:15:59,623 --> 01:16:01,697
Larita is your type,
isn't she, Father?

1038
01:16:01,832 --> 01:16:04,368
That is the nicest thing
any of you have ever said.

1039
01:16:04,501 --> 01:16:07,036
Hello, are we having a picnic?

1040
01:16:08,713 --> 01:16:14,378
John... I think your wife better unveil
this one herself. Don't you, Larita?

1041
01:16:18,098 --> 01:16:19,638
Before we met...

1042
01:16:20,725 --> 01:16:24,849
...I was involved in a court case
over the death of my husband.

1043
01:16:24,979 --> 01:16:27,302
It was seedy and stressful,

1044
01:16:27,439 --> 01:16:30,354
but since I was found innocent

1045
01:16:30,483 --> 01:16:33,600
I didn't think it necessary
to burden you with the details.

1046
01:16:33,736 --> 01:16:35,015
Innocent?

1047
01:16:35,154 --> 01:16:38,068
She was responsible
for a man killing himself!

1048
01:16:38,198 --> 01:16:41,813
The verdict was suicide
but that's not where it started.

1049
01:16:41,951 --> 01:16:43,741
I thought it was cancer.

1050
01:16:44,412 --> 01:16:46,035
It was...

1051
01:16:46,164 --> 01:16:48,699
But he was so desperately sick.

1052
01:16:48,833 --> 01:16:52,033
If you'd known him, you would've
understood how forgivable it was.

1053
01:16:52,169 --> 01:16:54,622
It's not as if she poisoned him.
- That's what everyone thinks.

1054
01:16:54,755 --> 01:16:57,161
She's a black widow.
- I pity you, Marion.

1055
01:16:57,298 --> 01:16:59,502
Really? Well, I won't let you!

1056
01:16:59,634 --> 01:17:04,007
Right, that's it! You have a dance
to organise, I suggest you all get to it!

1057
01:17:04,138 --> 01:17:05,797
Now!

1058
01:17:09,727 --> 01:17:12,298
Hilda! Come on, inside!

1059
01:17:14,648 --> 01:17:16,473
John...

1060
01:17:41,922 --> 01:17:45,039
Are you crying
because you're angry or ashamed?

1061
01:17:47,176 --> 01:17:48,669
Neither.

1062
01:17:50,347 --> 01:17:54,803
Coming here has been the most
demoralising experience of my life.

1063
01:18:00,022 --> 01:18:03,103
Why didn't you tell me?

1064
01:18:03,233 --> 01:18:05,769
I wanted to,
everything just happened so fast.

1065
01:18:05,902 --> 01:18:08,058
That's not good enough.

1066
01:18:09,405 --> 01:18:12,273
I tried to, several times.

1067
01:18:14,077 --> 01:18:17,987
But you trusted me..."absolutely".

1068
01:18:19,999 --> 01:18:23,945
And you saw the field day
those fatuous hypocrites made of it.

1069
01:18:24,086 --> 01:18:26,077
Please remember they're my family.

1070
01:18:26,212 --> 01:18:28,783
I shouldn't think of them at all
if they weren't.

1071
01:18:28,922 --> 01:18:33,248
Still... you should have told me.

1072
01:18:34,844 --> 01:18:36,918
You should have loved me more.

1073
01:18:39,015 --> 01:18:41,171
I couldn't love you any more.

1074
01:18:41,310 --> 01:18:43,881
You should have loved me better.

1075
01:18:47,023 --> 01:18:49,310
I don't understand you, Larita.

1076
01:18:51,401 --> 01:18:53,937
I don't understand you at all.

1077
01:19:15,256 --> 01:19:19,712
1... 2... 3... Are you all left feet?

1078
01:19:19,843 --> 01:19:23,920
Dancing with you
is like trying to move a piano.

1079
01:19:24,056 --> 01:19:26,426
I wonder what the American
will be wearing.

1080
01:19:26,558 --> 01:19:28,798
Or who she'll be poisoning!

1081
01:19:31,604 --> 01:19:35,016
Do you like long, moonlit walks?

1082
01:19:35,149 --> 01:19:37,720
Only when taken by people
who annoy me.

1083
01:19:37,860 --> 01:19:41,854
You've got me all to yourself.
Larita's upstairs with a headache.

1084
01:19:41,988 --> 01:19:45,318
And which little fool, pray tell,
gave her that?

1085
01:20:02,591 --> 01:20:06,170
You ought to see if Larita is coping.
- I already have. She's fine.

1086
01:20:06,302 --> 01:20:09,917
It's been a very trying day
for her, John.

1087
01:20:10,055 --> 01:20:13,053
Go and escort your wife down.
- No, I wouldn't worry.

1088
01:20:13,183 --> 01:20:16,963
You know my wife, she'll make
an entrance when she's ready.

1089
01:20:22,066 --> 01:20:23,891
Come in.

1090
01:20:26,570 --> 01:20:29,604
Quickly, you'll blow my cover.

1091
01:20:37,496 --> 01:20:40,115
Why are you sitting in the dark?

1092
01:20:40,249 --> 01:20:42,205
Watching.

1093
01:20:43,794 --> 01:20:46,958
People are so universally similar
when their guard is down.

1094
01:20:47,088 --> 01:20:50,370
Oh, hello! Ha-ha!

1095
01:20:53,512 --> 01:20:57,671
It seems they are universally similar
when their guard is up, as well.

1096
01:21:00,726 --> 01:21:02,183
May I?

1097
01:21:04,229 --> 01:21:08,519
Thank you for being gallant today.
- You are damn cool in a crisis.

1098
01:21:09,943 --> 01:21:13,143
The judge at my trial
said something similar.

1099
01:21:15,322 --> 01:21:17,478
Why did you do it?

1100
01:21:20,034 --> 01:21:22,487
Why did you marry John?

1101
01:21:24,038 --> 01:21:27,700
My first husband was older,
and his end was messy.

1102
01:21:29,752 --> 01:21:31,956
Long afterwards, this...

1103
01:21:33,588 --> 01:21:34,915
...boy...

1104
01:21:35,048 --> 01:21:40,204
...this pure boy arrived
fresh and unblemished.

1105
01:21:43,431 --> 01:21:46,843
I married him because
any other relationship seemed...

1106
01:21:47,726 --> 01:21:50,511
...cheap and squalid.

1107
01:21:52,314 --> 01:21:56,805
My first marriage cost me my youth,
and here I am stealing someone else's.

1108
01:21:58,861 --> 01:22:00,520
What will you do?

1109
01:22:02,615 --> 01:22:04,819
The best I can.

1110
01:22:10,873 --> 01:22:12,152
Oh, Davis, thank you.

1111
01:22:13,916 --> 01:22:17,080
And thank you, Pinkie.
- No, not at all, my dear.

1112
01:22:17,211 --> 01:22:19,830
Just look at this turnout.
- Hmm...

1113
01:22:19,963 --> 01:22:24,621
They've only come for a repeat
performance of the Cincinnati succubus.

1114
01:22:24,759 --> 01:22:27,129
May I have the pleasure?

1115
01:23:01,042 --> 01:23:02,239
Oh, look!

1116
01:23:21,435 --> 01:23:24,848
Tango, please.
- Certainly. Tango...

1117
01:23:32,779 --> 01:23:35,528
Dance with me, John.

1118
01:23:37,033 --> 01:23:39,189
Lari, don't.

1119
01:23:39,326 --> 01:23:42,774
Please? Dance with me.

1120
01:24:24,742 --> 01:24:27,231
That was very gallant.

1121
01:25:18,457 --> 01:25:21,574
You've got to stop them, Mother.
- No, I don't.

1122
01:26:00,495 --> 01:26:03,612
Oh, marvellous! Marvellous!

1123
01:26:05,416 --> 01:26:08,698
Straight from the bordellos
of Buenos Aires

1124
01:26:08,835 --> 01:26:12,201
to the Hippodrome of London, Maestro,
take it away!

1125
01:26:13,840 --> 01:26:17,171
Jim, this is the end.

1126
01:26:28,061 --> 01:26:29,968
Congratulations, Madam.

1127
01:26:30,104 --> 01:26:33,849
Have you been drinking, Furber?
- Yes, Madam. Prodigiously.

1128
01:26:33,983 --> 01:26:36,685
You are full of surprises.
- Oh, yes, Madam.

1129
01:26:36,819 --> 01:26:38,893
I was even arrested once.

1130
01:26:39,030 --> 01:26:40,937
What for?
- Bigamy.

1131
01:26:49,371 --> 01:26:52,369
Ah, there you are,
Pinkie, I've found you.

1132
01:27:03,176 --> 01:27:05,297
Larita, where are you going?

1133
01:27:05,428 --> 01:27:08,296
Away, Sarah. For John's sake.

1134
01:27:08,431 --> 01:27:10,173
Far, far away.

1135
01:27:11,308 --> 01:27:13,429
Is there anything I can do?

1136
01:27:13,560 --> 01:27:15,930
You can look after him.

1137
01:27:16,062 --> 01:27:19,724
Women like me are tiresome in love.
We expect too much.

1138
01:27:21,609 --> 01:27:25,389
Marry John. It's the way things
always should've been.

1139
01:27:25,529 --> 01:27:30,233
I'm just so sorry I got in the way.
- You love him that much?

1140
01:27:36,789 --> 01:27:39,242
Go. I'll cover for you.

1141
01:27:39,375 --> 01:27:41,082
Sweet Sarah.

1142
01:27:41,210 --> 01:27:44,457
So glad you've recovered
from your headache.

1143
01:27:44,588 --> 01:27:47,539
Please don't build any convenient
social lies on my behalf.

1144
01:27:47,673 --> 01:27:52,247
I say, Mother is only...
- Fighting to keep the charade alive?

1145
01:27:52,387 --> 01:27:55,752
You've shown tremendous fortitude
holding this family together, Veronica,

1146
01:27:55,890 --> 01:27:57,679
and I can respect that.

1147
01:27:57,808 --> 01:28:02,513
What I can't respect is the manipulative
road you've chosen to maintain control.

1148
01:28:02,645 --> 01:28:05,927
This war is over. Move on.

1149
01:28:06,066 --> 01:28:08,601
"Move on." Oh, how convenient.

1150
01:28:08,734 --> 01:28:13,107
Oh, wake up, Marion.
Edgar's not coming back.

1151
01:28:13,238 --> 01:28:15,359
And that ring isn't stuck, you are.

1152
01:28:15,490 --> 01:28:20,112
And Hilda, you've got such promise,
yet you're squandering it on malice.

1153
01:28:20,245 --> 01:28:22,152
My advice to both you girls?

1154
01:28:23,081 --> 01:28:26,945
Run! Go see the world
through your own eyes.

1155
01:28:28,586 --> 01:28:32,165
So speaks the siren,
leading the sailors to their death.

1156
01:28:32,297 --> 01:28:35,544
At least I'm not Medusa,
turning them to stone.

1157
01:28:35,675 --> 01:28:39,800
Get out!
- Larita? Lari?

1158
01:28:40,680 --> 01:28:43,631
Lari, don't go.
- John, I have to.

1159
01:28:43,766 --> 01:28:47,214
I can't live here. Nothing can.

1160
01:28:47,352 --> 01:28:50,884
But you're my wife, and I love you.

1161
01:28:52,274 --> 01:28:54,348
Oh, John, my darling...

1162
01:28:56,487 --> 01:28:59,105
You don't know what love is.

1163
01:28:59,239 --> 01:29:03,564
You have no idea what it means
to love someone so much

1164
01:29:03,701 --> 01:29:06,403
that you will do anything for them.

1165
01:29:10,249 --> 01:29:12,916
Even inject them with poison

1166
01:29:13,042 --> 01:29:16,573
when they were too feeble
to do it for themselves.

1167
01:29:22,258 --> 01:29:25,540
I don't believe that you could've
ever loved me like that.

1168
01:29:34,228 --> 01:29:36,053
Oh, John, let her go.

1169
01:29:38,858 --> 01:29:44,439
Let her go, off into the sunset
to inject another family with her poison!

1170
01:29:44,571 --> 01:29:46,562
Mother...
Off you go!

1171
01:29:46,697 --> 01:29:49,067
Before your past
catches up with you... again!

1172
01:29:49,199 --> 01:29:50,905
Mother!

1173
01:29:53,453 --> 01:29:55,776
Oh, you evil...

1174
01:29:55,914 --> 01:29:58,070
Mother! Shut up!

1175
01:30:01,335 --> 01:30:03,824
They are predicting warmer weather,
Madam.

1176
01:30:03,962 --> 01:30:07,079
Yes, Furber, I believe they are.
Thank you.

1177
01:30:12,304 --> 01:30:13,761
Very generous.

1178
01:30:15,056 --> 01:30:18,303
There's something special in there
for Jackson. Make sure he gets it.

1179
01:30:18,434 --> 01:30:21,349
Of course.
Where will Madam be staying?

1180
01:30:22,396 --> 01:30:23,853
Who knows?

1181
01:30:24,606 --> 01:30:26,147
Good luck.

1182
01:30:27,401 --> 01:30:29,142
And you, Furber.

1183
01:30:30,111 --> 01:30:32,682
Would you forward the painting please,
